core.game.callback
Class CallBackBufferedObject

java.lang.Object
  core.game.callback.CallBackBufferedObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
CallBackBuffered, java.lang.Runnable
public class CallBackBufferedObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable, CallBackBuffered

this object implements the CallBackBuffered interface, and is the basis from which classes that wish to act as callback operators extend.

Author:
Mike

Field Summary
protected  CallBackBuffer callbackbuffer
          the callback buffer object
protected  long callbackcheckinterval
          the sleep interval used in the default run operation this value is 200 ms by default, as specified in the empty constructor

          the Thread used by this object
 
Constructor Summary
CallBackBufferedObject()
          creates a new CallBackBufferedObject, and starts its thread, which sends it into a loop that checks the buffer and then goes to sleep for a specified number of milliseconds

          creates a new CallBackBufferedObject, and starts its thread, which sends it into a loop that checks the buffer and then goes to sleep for a specified number of milliseconds
